				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Lost &amp; Found (fan expansion for The 7th Continent)" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Lost &amp;amp; Found is an unofficial fan-made print-and-play mini-expansion for The 7th Continent.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Many things and even more people got lost on the 7th continent.&amp;#10;Some want to be found, some do not, and some should not.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It's primarily meant for the players who &amp;quot;have seen it all&amp;quot;, as it brings new uses for the old places and familiar items. Good knowledge of the continent will come in handy, however, there are enough hints that you shouldn't get completely lost even without previous experience.&amp;#10;If you want to learn more about the theme read the Clue card on the first page of the PNP to discover more.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The expansion contains 2 modules:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     You can play with the new curse &amp;quot;The Lost Artefact&amp;quot;, alone or alongside any other curses. It is a medium length curse (~10 hours), with multiple parallel objectives.&amp;#10;     You can add the &amp;quot;Book of Idols&amp;quot; card to your game, even when not playing with the new curse, in the same way, you would add the &amp;quot;Pocket Watch&amp;quot; from the &amp;quot;Path Of Repentance&amp;quot; expansion.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;General features:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Compatible with all editions of the base game and all the official expansions.&amp;#10;     No cards from this expansion are ever shuffled with the original cards (so you don't have to worry about matching backs etc.). There is no new Curse card included, for this very reason.&amp;#10;     The Blue Adventure cards form their own deck with green and golden numbered cards the only difference is that their &amp;quot;numbox&amp;quot; is blue.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contents:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     1 Rules card&amp;#10;     1 Clue card for the new curse of &amp;quot;The Lost Artefact&amp;quot;&amp;#10;     1 &amp;quot;Book of Idols&amp;quot; card&amp;#10;     90 Blue Adventure Cards, forming the separate Blue Adventure Deck&amp;#10;     You can also print your own 000 and 100 blue dividers&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
